message: Welcome, future crafter! Here's what I learned: The 'scissors' tool is great for 'soft' items (like paper, flowers, leaves, feathers, ribbon, sponge, mushroom, yarn) â€“ it adds a 'cut' feature and increases their value to 25. Avoid using 'scissors' on 'hard' items (like shells, buttons, bark, beads) as this destroys them and gives negative value. The 'frame' tool is best used on 'cut' 'soft' items. Framing a 'cut' item (e.g., 'cut paper', 'cut flower') consistently boosts its value to 45. This was the highest value I achieved. Be careful with combining already framed items; I found that doing so often resulted in a ruined frame and negative value. My strategy for high scores was to 'cut' all soft items, then 'frame' all the 'cut' soft items, and then submit. Good luck!
